    {
      "name": "DETAIL",
      "description": "Detail",
      "help": "Detail (DETAIL)\n\nSpecifies which set of attributes is shown for each object.\n\nNote: When the output is directed to a database file and a value of *BASIC, *FULL or *SERVICE is specified, all object attribute information is written to the file.\n\n指定できる特殊値: *BASIC, *FULL, *SERVICE, *NAME, *TEXTATR",
      "inputType": "text",
      "required": false,
      "defaultValue": "*BASIC",
      "attributes": {
        "characterSet": "upper",
        "maxLength": 10
      },
      "positional": 3,
      "basic": true,
      "valueMap": {
        "*BASIC": "B",
        "*FULL": "F",
        "*NAME": "N",
        "*SERVICE": "S",
        "*TEXTATR": "T"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "ASPDEV",
      "description": "ASP device",
      "help": "ASP device (ASPDEV)\n\nSpecifies the auxiliary storage pool (ASP) device name where storage is allocated for the library containing the object. If the library resides in an ASP that is not part of the thread's library name space, this parameter must be specified to ensure the correct library is searched. If this parameter is used when the library qualifier specified for the Object (OBJ) parameter is *CURLIB, *LIBL, or *USRLIBL, ASPDEV(*) is the only valid value. This parameter can be specified as a single value or a list of one or two elements.\n\nSingle values\n\nElement 1: Device\n\nSpecify the name of the primary or secondary ASP device to be searched. The primary or secondary ASP must have been activated (by varying on the ASP device) and have a status of 'Available'. The system ASP (ASP 1) and defined basic user ASPs (ASPs 2-32) will not be searched.\n\nNote: To specify a specific auxiliary storage pool (ASP) device name when the search type specified for element 2 is *ASP, you must have execute (*EXECUTE) authority for the specific ASP device.\n\nTo specify a specific auxiliary storage pool (ASP) device name when the search type specified for element 2 is *ASPGRP, you must have execute (*EXECUTE) authority for each ASP device in the ASP group.\n\nElement 2: Search type\n\nSpecifies whether the single ASP device or the entire ASP group named in element 1 is to be searched.",
      "inputType": "group",
      "required": false,
      "groupKind": "elements",
      "singleValues": [
        "*ALLAVL",
        "*CURASPGRP",
        "*SYSBAS"
      ],
      "children": [
        {
          "name": "ASPDEV",
          "description": "Device",
          "inputType": "text",
          "required": false,
          "attributes": {
            "characterSet": "upper",
            "maxLength": 10
          },
          "defaultValue": "*",
          "placeholder": "*"
        },
        {
          "name": "SCHTYPE",
          "description": "Search type",
          "inputType": "dropdown",
          "required": false,
          "defaultValue": "*ASP",
          "attributes": {
            "characterSet": "upper"
